148â†’/**
149â†’ * Parses a substring of the receiver string as a positive ASCII integer.
150â†’ *
151â†’ * All characters between [start] (inclusive) and [end] (exclusive) must be ASCII digits,
152â†’ * and the size of the substring must be at most 9, but the function does not check it.
